01:16:21.435 --> 01:16:22.871
You gotta straighten this thing out.

1132
01:16:22.895 --> 01:16:26.147
We got to have calm now. We don't know
what the hell she's gonna do.

1133
01:16:26.315 --> 01:16:28.566
She's getting all hysterical.
She gets very excited.

1134
01:16:28.734 --> 01:16:32.612
She's wild. And you got to take it easy.
You got children.

1135
01:16:33.572 --> 01:16:36.949
I'm not saying you gotta back to her
this minute, but you gotta go back.

1136
01:16:37.117 --> 01:16:39.577
It's the only way.
You gotta keep up appearances.

1137
01:16:39.745 --> 01:16:42.205
The two of them
come over every day, commiserating.

1138
01:16:42.372 --> 01:16:44.332
I can't have it.

1139
01:16:45.501 --> 01:16:47.835
I can't do it, Henry.

1140
01:16:48.003 --> 01:16:51.088
Nobody says that you can't do
what you wanna do.

1141
01:16:51.256 --> 01:16:53.883
We all know that. I
mean, this is what it is.

1142
01:16:54.051 --> 01:16:56.802
We know what it is.
You have to do the right thing.

1143
01:16:56.970 --> 01:16:59.305
You have to go home to the family,
you understand?

1144
01:16:59.473 --> 01:17:02.099
You got to go home, okay? Look at me.

1145
01:17:02.392 --> 01:17:04.602
You gotta go home. Smarten up.

1146
01:17:05.312 --> 01:17:06.854
- All right?
- All right.

1147
01:17:07.022 --> 01:17:08.564
I'm gonna talk to Karen.

1148
01:17:08.732 --> 01:17:12.276
I'll straighten this out.
I know just what to say to her.

1149
01:17:12.778 --> 01:17:14.779
I'm gonna tell her you'll go back to her...

1150
01:17:14.947 --> 01:17:17.823
and it'll be just the way
it was when you were first married...

1151
01:17:17.991 --> 01:17:19.867
your romance, it's gonna be beautiful.

1152
01:17:20.035 --> 01:17:22.036
I know how to talk to her,
especially to her.

1153
01:17:22.204 --> 01:17:24.664
Jimmy and Tommy are going down
to Tampa this weekend...

1154
01:17:24.831 --> 01:17:25.957
to pick up something for me.

1155
01:17:26.124 --> 01:17:27.833
Instead, you go with Jimmy.

1156
01:17:28.001 --> 01:17:29.293
You come with me, we'll go down.

1157
01:17:29.461 --> 01:17:31.963
Have a good time.
Take some time for yourself. Relax.

1158
01:17:32.130 --> 01:17:33.965
Sit in the sun. Take a couple days off.

1159
01:17:34.132 --> 01:17:35.967
- We'll have a good time.
- Enjoy yourselves.

1160
01:17:36.134 --> 01:17:39.262
And when you come back,
you go back to Karen. Huh?

1161
01:17:39.429 --> 01:17:41.138
Please, there's no other way.

1162
01:17:41.306 --> 01:17:43.891
You're not gonna get a divorce.
We're not <i>animali.</i>

1163
01:17:44.059 --> 01:17:46.644
No divorce. She'll never divorce him.

1164
01:17:48.438 --> 01:17:51.315
She'll kill him, but she won't divorce him.

1165
01:17:55.654 --> 01:17:57.321
{\an8}You gonna pay us?

1166
01:18:03.662 --> 01:18:06.706
- You gonna pay?
- Give us the fucking money!

1167
01:18:06.873 --> 01:18:09.292
I can't, I swear.

1168
01:18:10.836 --> 01:18:12.128
Let's go.

1169
01:18:20.679 --> 01:18:23.347
- We'll throw the bastard to the lions.
- No!

1170
01:18:23.515 --> 01:18:26.225
What fucking lions?
I ain't going near any lions, Jimmy!

1171
01:18:26.393 --> 01:18:28.728
- Let's throw him over the moat.
- All right.

1172
01:18:28.895 --> 01:18:30.271
I'll get the money!

1173
01:18:30.439 --> 01:18:33.065
<i>They must really feed each other
to the lions down there...</i>

1174
01:18:33.233 --> 01:18:34.984
<i>because the guy gave the money right up.</i>

1175
01:18:35.152 --> 01:18:36.777
I swear to Christ, I'll get the money.

1176
01:18:36.945 --> 01:18:39.071
<i>We got to spend the rest of the weekend
at the track.</i>

1177
01:18:39.698 --> 01:18:40.823
Yeah. They mean business.

1178
01:18:40.991 --> 01:18:43.618
<i>Then, I couldn't believe what happened.</i>

1179
01:18:44.036 --> 01:18:46.537
<i>When we got home,
we were all over the newspaper.</i>

1180
01:18:46.705 --> 01:18:49.915
<i>At first, I didn't even know
why we got picked up.</i>

1181
01:18:50.083 --> 01:18:52.209
<i>Then I found out
that the guy we roughed up...</i>

1182
01:18:52.377 --> 01:18:55.755
<i>turned out to have a sister
working as a typist for the FBI.</i>

1183
01:18:55.922 --> 01:18:58.716
<i>Who could believe it?
Of all the fucking people.</i>

1184
01:18:58.884 --> 01:19:02.178
<i>She gave up everybody:
Jimmy, me, even her brother.</i>

1185
01:19:03.555 --> 01:19:06.432
<i>It took the jury six hours
to bring us in guilty.</i>

1186
01:19:06.600 --> 01:19:09.852
<i>The judge gave Jimmy and me 10 years
like he was giving away candy.</i>

1187
01:19:10.020 --> 01:19:12.688
...ten years in a federal penitentiary.

1188
01:19:12.898 --> 01:19:15.858
You will now be turned over to the
United States Attorney General's Office.

1189
01:19:21.239 --> 01:19:22.865
Toast, guys.

1190
01:19:23.033 --> 01:19:25.368
Good trip, good life, get out soon.

1191
01:19:25.535 --> 01:19:27.411
Good trip, sweetheart.

1192
01:19:30.332 --> 01:19:32.416
We'll watch the home front.

1193
01:19:33.919 --> 01:19:36.379
Say hello to those blow-job hacks.

1194
01:19:37.422 --> 01:19:40.591
Yeah, motherfuck them
every chance you get.

1195
01:19:46.431 --> 01:19:48.974
I'll call you when I get a chance.

1196
01:20:01.363 --> 01:20:02.655
Now take me to jail.

1197
01:20:07.327 --> 01:20:10.121
<i>In prison, dinner was always a big thing.</i>

1198
01:20:10.455 --> 01:20:13.999
<i>We had a pasta course,
and then we had a meat or a fish.</i>

1199
01:20:14.543 --> 01:20:17.461
<i>Paulie did the prep work.
He was doing a year for contempt...</i>

1200
01:20:17.629 --> 01:20:19.964
<i>and had this wonderful system
for doing the garlic.</i>

1201
01:20:20.132 --> 01:20:23.134
<i>He used a razor,
and he used to slice it so thin...</i>

1202
01:20:23.301 --> 01:20:26.095
<i>that it used to liquefy in the pan
with just a little oil.</i>

1203
01:20:26.263 --> 01:20:28.222
<i>It was a very good system.</i>

1204
01:20:28.390 --> 01:20:30.891
<i>Vinnie was in charge of the tomato sauce.</i>

1205
01:20:31.059 --> 01:20:32.476
Get the smell?

1206
01:20:32.644 --> 01:20:35.354
Three kinds of meat in the meatballs:

1207
01:20:35.522 --> 01:20:37.565
Veal, beef, and pork.

1208
01:20:37.941 --> 01:20:40.025
Good, but you gotta have the pork.

1209
01:20:40.193 --> 01:20:41.736
That's the flavor.

1210
01:20:41.903 --> 01:20:45.364
<i>I felt he used too many onions,
but it was still a very good sauce.</i>

1211
01:20:45.532 --> 01:20:48.325
Vinnie, don't put too many onions
in the sauce.

1212
01:20:48.493 --> 01:20:51.078
I didn't put too much onions in, Paul.

1213
01:20:51.371 --> 01:20:53.164
Put three small onions, that's all I did.

1214
01:20:53.331 --> 01:20:55.875
Three onions? How many cans
of tomatoes you put in there?

1215
01:20:56.042 --> 01:20:58.794
- I put two big cans.
- You don't need three onions.

1216
01:20:58.962 --> 01:21:00.963
<i>Johnny Dio did the meat.</i>

1217
01:21:01.131 --> 01:21:03.716
<i>We had no broiler,
so Johnny did everything in pans.</i>

1218
01:21:03.884 --> 01:21:06.010
<i>It used to smell up the joint
something awful...</i>

1219
01:21:06.178 --> 01:21:09.138
<i>and the hacks used to die,
but he still cooked a great steak.</i>

1220
01:21:09.306 --> 01:21:11.849
- How do you like yours?
- Medium rare.

1221
01:21:12.434 --> 01:21:14.560
Medium rare. An aristocrat.

1222
01:21:14.978 --> 01:21:18.731
<i>You know, when you think
of prison you get pictures in your mind...</i>

1223
01:21:18.899 --> 01:21:22.526
<i>of all those old movies
with rows of guys behind bars.</i>

1224
01:21:22.694 --> 01:21:24.612
<i>It wasn't like that for wiseguys.</i>

1225
01:21:24.780 --> 01:21:27.448
<i>It really wasn't that bad,
excepting that I missed Jimmy...</i>

1226
01:21:27.616 --> 01:21:29.033
<i>who was doing his time in Atlanta.</i>

1227
01:21:29.201 --> 01:21:31.702
Give me two steaks
while you're in there, all right?

1228
01:21:33.038 --> 01:21:37.500
<i>Everyone else in the joint was doing real
time, mixed together, living like pigs.</i>

1229
01:21:37.667 --> 01:21:40.669
<i>But we lived alone. We owned the joint.</i>

1230
01:21:40.837 --> 01:21:44.215
We batted them sons of bitches.
You couldn't recognize them.

1231
01:21:44.382 --> 01:21:45.716
Good, they deserved it.

1232
01:21:45.884 --> 01:21:49.178
<i>Even the hacks we couldn't bribe
would never rat on the guys we did.</i>

1233
01:21:49.346 --> 01:21:51.305
...had respect. People loved one another.

1234
01:21:51.473 --> 01:21:53.682
- They left their doors open.
- Sorry it took so long.

1235
01:21:53.850 --> 01:21:56.352
The skinny guard's getting to be
a real pain in the ass.

1236
01:21:56.520 --> 01:21:59.730
- We're gonna have to do something.
- I took care of him.

1237
01:21:59.898 --> 01:22:01.607
What'd you bring?

1238
01:22:01.775 --> 01:22:03.901
- Bread.
- Good. Fresh.

1239
01:22:04.069 --> 01:22:05.861
Vinnie, I got your peppers and onions.

1240
01:22:06.029 --> 01:22:08.322
Salami, prosciutto, a lot of cheese.

1241
01:22:08.490 --> 01:22:09.990
Come on, what else?

1242
01:22:10.158 --> 01:22:11.659
- Scotch.
- Nice.

1243
01:22:12.661 --> 01:22:14.495
- Some red wine.
- Okay.

1244
01:22:14.830 --> 01:22:16.705
- Now we can eat.
- I got some white, too.

1245
01:22:16.873 --> 01:22:18.624
Give me the white, too. Beautiful.

1246
01:22:18.792 --> 01:22:21.794
Okay, boys, let's eat.
Come on, it's ready, Vinnie.

1247
01:22:22.379 --> 01:22:23.462
Some more bread.

1248
01:22:23.630 --> 01:22:26.298
Tomorrow we eat sandwiches.
You got to go on a diet, Vinnie.

1249
01:22:26.466 --> 01:22:28.551
- You must be kidding.
- Believe me.

1250
01:22:37.811 --> 01:22:39.436
What are you doing?

1251
01:22:44.568 --> 01:22:46.443
I'll take that.

1252
01:22:48.822 --> 01:22:51.282
- All right, I'll catch you guys later.
- Yeah.

1253
01:22:51.449 --> 01:22:53.784
You going for a walk in the park?

1254
01:22:55.287 --> 01:22:58.455
- Okay, I'll catch you next week. Thanks.
- Okay.

1255
01:23:01.293 --> 01:23:03.836
- Is there any more?
- No, that's it. Have a good weekend.

1256
01:23:04.004 --> 01:23:05.044
- Thanks.
- You too, Henry.

1257
01:23:13.930 --> 01:23:15.055
Mrs. Hill, come here.

1258
01:23:15.223 --> 01:23:16.390
Come on.

1259
01:23:19.769 --> 01:23:21.812
You girls stay right here.

1260
01:23:22.230 --> 01:23:25.482
- I want you to hold hands.
- Okay, go right up to the front.

1261
01:23:25.817 --> 01:23:27.735
- Let's go.
- How you doing?

1262
01:23:27.903 --> 01:23:30.321
- Good, how are you?
- Very well, thank you.

1263
01:23:42.375 --> 01:23:44.835
- What you talking about?
- I saw her name in the register.

1264
01:23:45.003 --> 01:23:47.171
- Jesus Christ.
- You want her to visit you?

1265
01:23:47.339 --> 01:23:51.008
Let her stay up all night crying
and writing letters to the parole board.

1266
01:23:51.176 --> 01:23:54.345
What am I doing here?
Where am I? I'm in jail.

1267
01:23:54.512 --> 01:23:56.722
I can't stop people
from coming to see me.

1268
01:23:56.890 --> 01:24:00.184
Good, let her sneak this stuff in
for you every week.

1269
01:24:00.352 --> 01:24:03.979
- Let her fight these bastards every week!
- Look what you're doing! Stop it!

1270
01:24:05.732 --> 01:24:07.691
- Shh.
- I'm sorry.

1271
01:24:08.193 --> 01:24:10.653
Let her sneak this shit in for you.

1272
01:24:11.696 --> 01:24:13.530
Will you stop it, Karen?

1273
01:24:13.990 --> 01:24:16.533
- Let her do it!
- Stop it!

1274
01:24:24.709 --> 01:24:28.087
Nobody's helping me. I'm all alone.

1275
01:24:29.047 --> 01:24:31.048
Belle and Morrie are broke.

1276
01:24:31.466 --> 01:24:34.677
I asked your friend Remo
for the money that he owes you.

1277
01:24:34.844 --> 01:24:36.220
You know what he told me?

1278
01:24:36.388 --> 01:24:39.974
He told me to take my kids down
to the police station and get on welfare.

1279
01:24:40.141 --> 01:24:42.101
It's gonna be okay.

1280
01:24:42.310 --> 01:24:46.397
Even Paulie, since he got out, I've never
seen him. I never see anybody anymore.

1281
01:24:46.564 --> 01:24:49.358
It's only you and me.
That's what happens when you go away.

1282
01:24:49.526 --> 01:24:53.529
I told you that we're on our own.
Forget everybody else. Forget Paulie.

1283
01:24:54.531 --> 01:24:58.534
As long as he's on parole,
he doesn't want anybody doing anything.

1284
01:25:00.996 --> 01:25:03.247
- I can't do it.
- Yes, you can. Listen to me.

1285
01:25:03.415 --> 01:25:06.000
All I need is for you
is to keep bringing me the stuff.

1286
01:25:06.167 --> 01:25:08.752
I got a guy in here from Pittsburgh
who'll help me move it.

1287
01:25:08.920 --> 01:25:10.546
In a month we're gonna be fine.

1288
01:25:10.714 --> 01:25:13.132
- We won't need anybody.
- I'm afraid.

1289
01:25:13.299 --> 01:25:15.259
I'm afraid if Paulie finds out...

1290
01:25:15.427 --> 01:25:16.719
Don't worry about him.

1291
01:25:16.886 --> 01:25:20.431
He is not helping us out.
Is he putting any food on the table?

1292
01:25:21.599 --> 01:25:23.058
We've gotta help each other.

1293
01:25:23.226 --> 01:25:26.895
We've just gotta be really careful
while we do it.

1294
01:25:31.568 --> 01:25:33.777
I don't want to hear a word
about her anymore.

1295
01:25:33.945 --> 01:25:34.945
Never.

1296
01:26:00.346 --> 01:26:02.014
Daddy!

1297
01:26:03.641 --> 01:26:05.893
- We missed you.
- Are you here to stay?

1298
01:26:06.061 --> 01:26:09.646
Did you see our pictures?
I did the one with the house and rainbow.

1299
01:26:09.814 --> 01:26:11.231
I did the sun.

1300
01:26:11.399 --> 01:26:15.319
My chorus concert is in two weeks.
Are you coming?

1301
01:26:16.154 --> 01:26:17.988
Do you like the house?

1302
01:26:19.282 --> 01:26:21.325
Karen, get packed.
We're moving out of here.

1303
01:26:21.493 --> 01:26:22.534
With what?

1304
01:26:22.744 --> 01:26:25.829
Don't worry, with what.
Just start looking for a new house.

1305
01:26:25.997 --> 01:26:29.416
I got to go to Pittsburgh in the morning.
Those guys there owe me $15,000.

1306
01:26:29.584 --> 01:26:31.502
We'll be all right. I got things lined up.

1307
01:26:31.669 --> 01:26:34.338
Pittsburgh? You have to go see
your parole officer tomorrow.

1308
01:26:34.506 --> 01:26:37.424
Don't worry about it.
Everything's gonna be fine.

1309
01:26:38.134 --> 01:26:40.511
- Who wants to go to Uncle Paulie's?
- Me!

1310
01:26:50.814 --> 01:26:52.397
What do you want?

1311
01:26:52.649 --> 01:26:54.691
Sweetheart, let Mommy eat.

1312
01:26:58.154 --> 01:27:01.031
You look good.
Did you eat this good in the joint?

1313
01:27:03.159 --> 01:27:05.035
I don't want any more of that shit.

1314
01:27:05.203 --> 01:27:06.203
What shit?

1315
01:27:06.371 --> 01:27:08.956
- Just stay away from the garbage.
- Look, Paulie...

1316
01:27:09.124 --> 01:27:12.334
I'm not talking about what you did inside.
You did what you had to do.

1317
01:27:12.502 --> 01:27:15.045
I'm talking about now. From now.
Here and now.

1318
01:27:16.089 --> 01:27:18.841
- Why would I get into that?
- Don't make a jerk out of me.

1319
01:27:19.008 --> 01:27:20.551
Just don't do it.

1320
01:27:24.305 --> 01:27:27.266
I want to talk to you about Jimmy.
You gotta watch out for him.

1321
01:27:27.433 --> 01:27:30.185
He's a good earner, but he's wild,
takes too many chances.

1322
01:27:30.353 --> 01:27:32.813
I know Jimmy. You think
I would take chances like him?

1323
01:27:32.981 --> 01:27:34.731
Tommy's a good kid, but he's crazy.

1324
01:27:34.899 --> 01:27:36.650
He's a cowboy.
He's got too much to prove.

1325
01:27:36.818 --> 01:27:38.443
You gotta watch out for kids like this.

1326
01:27:38.611 --> 01:27:41.238
I know what they are.
I only use them for certain things.

1327
01:27:41.406 --> 01:27:43.907
I ain't gonna get fucked like Gribbs,
you understand?

1328
01:27:44.075 --> 01:27:48.412
Gribbs is 70 years old. The fucking guy's
gonna die in prison. I don't need that.

1329
01:27:48.746 --> 01:27:52.624
So I'm warning everybody. Everybody.
Could be my son, could be anybody.

1330
01:27:53.168 --> 01:27:55.711
Gribbs got 20 years just
for saying hello to some fuck...

1331
01:27:55.879 --> 01:27:57.963
who was sneaking behind his back,
selling junk.

1332
01:27:58.131 --> 01:28:00.591
I don't need that.
That won't happen to me, understand?

1333
01:28:00.758 --> 01:28:02.885
You know you're out early
because I got you a job.

1334
01:28:03.052 --> 01:28:05.053
I don't need this heat,
you understand that?

1335
01:28:05.221 --> 01:28:09.099
You see anybody fucking around
with this shit you're gonna tell me, right?

1336
01:28:09.267 --> 01:28:10.392
That means anybody.

1337
01:28:10.560 --> 01:28:11.560
- All right.
- Yeah?

1338
01:28:11.728 --> 01:28:13.228
Yeah. Of course.

1339
01:28:20.820 --> 01:28:22.779
<i>Took me about a week
of sneaking around...</i>

1340
01:28:22.947 --> 01:28:24.781
<i>before I could unload
the Pittsburgh stuff.</i>

1341
01:28:24.949 --> 01:28:27.409
<i>But when I did, it was a real score.</i>

1342
01:28:27.577 --> 01:28:30.120
<i>I started using Sandy's place
to mix the stuff.</i>

1343
01:28:30.288 --> 01:28:32.706
<i>And even with Sandy snorting
more than she mixed...</i>

1344
01:28:32.874 --> 01:28:35.500
<i>I could see that
this was a really good business.</i>

1345
01:28:35.668 --> 01:28:38.086
<i>I made $12,000 in my second week.</i>

1346
01:28:38.671 --> 01:28:41.757
<i>I had a down payment on my house
and things were really rolling.</i>

1347
01:28:41.925 --> 01:28:46.136
<i>All I had to do was every once in a while
tell Sandy that I loved her.</i>

1348
01:28:49.766 --> 01:28:51.808
<i>But it was perfect, I'm telling you.</i>

1349
01:28:51.976 --> 01:28:54.353
<i>As long as I kept getting
the stuff from Pittsburgh...</i>

1350
01:28:54.520 --> 01:28:56.230
<i>I knew Paulie would never find out.</i>

1351
01:28:56.397 --> 01:29:00.317
<i>Within a couple of weeks,
